<p><b>Eliyahu Moshe Goldratt</b> (born August 15, 1948) is an Israeli physicist who became a business management guru.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> He is the originator of the Optimized Production Technology, the <a href="/wiki/Theory_of_Constraints" title="Theory of Constraints">Theory of Constraints</a> (TOC), the <a href="/wiki/Thinking_Processes_(Theory_of_Constraints)" title="Thinking Processes (Theory of Constraints)" class="mw-redirect">Thinking Processes</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Drum-Buffer-Rope&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Drum-Buffer-Rope (page does not exist)">Drum-Buffer-Rope</a>, <a href="/wiki/Critical_Chain_Project_Management" title="Critical Chain Project Management">Critical Chain Project Management</a> (CCPM) and other TOC derived tools.</p>
<p>He has authored several <a href="/wiki/Business_fable" title="Business fable">business novels</a> and non-fiction works, mainly on the Theory of Constraints.</p>
